title: Ikea's new Stockholm collection: Sneak peek - AOL Lifestyle
text:
Lynsey Eidell Feb 21st 2017 11:52AM 
ICYMI: Ikea is no longer just for college dorm rooms. The Swedish retailer has been bringing the furniture fire for a while now, but its recent collections have been so good, we can hardly believe its Ikea. The latest collection to deliver some serious wow factor is the Stockholm collection, a carefully curated portfolio of 47 pieces with a focus on "slow living" (read: cozy, comfortable, handmade furniture). It doesn't hit stores until April, but this sneak peek offers a preview of some of Stockholm's best offeringsâ€”and we're already obsessed. You will be, too, after you catch a glimpse at these quality pieces that look expensive but still come at an affordable price. 7 PHOTOS
